.TH PODRADIO 1 "2025-03-29" "PodRadio V0.05B9n3e5g3n" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
podradio \- Terminal-based podcast and radio player
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B podradio
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
PodRadio is a powerful terminal-based podcast and radio player with an ncurses interface.
It supports TuneIn radio streaming, RSS podcast subscriptions, YouTube playback, and local media files.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.B \-a \fIURL\fR, \-\-add \fIURL\fR
Add a new subscription from the specified URL.
.TP
.B \-i \fIFILE\fR, \-\-import \fIFILE\fR
Import subscriptions from an OPML file.
.TP
.B \-e \fIFILE\fR, \-\-export \fIFILE\fR
Export subscriptions to an OPML file.
.TP
.B \-t \fITIME\fR, \-\-timer \fITIME\fR
Set a sleep timer. TIME can be in formats: 30m (30 minutes), 2h (2 hours), or 1:30:00 (1 hour 30 minutes).
.TP
.B \-\-purge
Clear all cached data and reset the application.
